    <strong>Example 1</strong>
    <br>
    <strong> Solution</strong>
    <br>
    A man saves $20000 in microfinance bank for one year, if the interest rate is 10% per annum. How much will he get at the end of the year?
    <br>
    <strong>Note; per annum means each year.</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    10% of $20000 = <sup>10</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x <sup>20000</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> = 10 x 200 = $2000
    <br>
    Interest = <b>$2000</b>
    <br>
     Amount at the end of the year = Amount saved + Interest
     <br>
     Amount at the end of the year = $20000 + $2000
    <br>
    Amount at the end of the year = <b>$22000</b>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
   <strong>Example 2</strong>
    <br>
    <strong> Solution</strong>
    <br>
    A trader borrows $2000 for 3 weeks at $1 on each $10 interest per week. How much is the trader paying back in total after 3 weeks?
    <br>
    <strong>Solution </strong>
    <br>
    Number of $10 in $2000 = <sup>$2000</sup>&frasl;<sub>$10</sub> = <strong>200</strong>
    <br>
    Interest per week = $1 x 200 = $200
    <br>
    Interest in 3 weeks = 3 x $200 = <b> $600 </b>
    <br>
    <strong>The total amount</strong> = Amount borrowed + Interest
    <br>
    = $2000 + $600
    <br>
    = $2600
    <br>
    Total amount = <b>$2600</b>
   </div>
