  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> What is Tax? </h3>
  </div>
<p>
<strong>Tax</strong> is a compulsory payment imposed on an individual or legal entity by government to raise money for
 government expenditures e.g. income tax such as, PAYE (<strong>pay-as-you-earn</strong>).
</p>
<p>
For any salary earner or wage earner, it is not the total income that is taxable;
<br>
<strong> Taxable income </strong> = total income – allowances.
</p>
<p>
<strong>The allowances are;</strong> personal allowance, child allowance, dependent relative allowance etc. 
The accurate conditions for 
calculating the tax would be given per income earner and it varies.
</p>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> How to Calculate the Income Tax </h3>
  </div>

<p>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
A staff has a total income of $5400 per month. He has 2 children; he claims $300 for dependent relatives. $700 for personal allowance and $250 for child allowance, If the bands for taxable income are; first $2000 attracts 10% tax rate, over $2000 - $4000 attracts 15% and over $4000 - $6000 attracts 20%. Calculate the amount of tax he pays.
<br>
<strong>Solutions</strong>
<br>
<strong>Total allowance </strong>= personal + dependent + child (allowances)
<br>
= 700 + 300 + 2(250)
<br>
= 700 + 300 + 500
<br>
Total allowance = <strong>$1500</strong>
<br>
<strong>Taxable income</strong> = total income – total allowances
<br>
= $5400 - $1500
<br>
Taxable income = <b>$3900</b>
<br>
Taxable in $3900 => $2000 + $1900
<br>
Tax he pays = <b>10% </b> of $2000 + <b>15% </b> of $1900
<br>
= $200 + $285
<br>
 Tax he pays = <b>$485</b>
</p>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> How to Calculate Discounts </h3>
</div>
