    <br>
    Drilling an oil well costs $14000, the driller gives 25% discount for cash. How much would customer pay?
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    Discount = 25% of $14000 = <sup>25</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x $14000 = 25 x 140 
    Discount = <strong>$3500</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>Actual payment</strong> = $14000 - $3500 = <strong>$10500</strong>
    </div>
