  <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> How to Calculate Value-Added-Tax (VAT) </h3>
  </div>
<p>
<strong>VAT (value-added-tax)</strong> is a tax on the selling price of certain items and services.
</p>
<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    <strong>Example 1</strong>
    <br>
    A tag is placed on a washing machine that the price is $1050 plus 5% VAT. How much does the customer pay?
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    VAT = 5% of $1050 = <sup>5</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x <sup>$1050</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> = <sup>5250</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> 
    <br>
    VAT = <strong> $52.5</strong>
    <br>
    Amount paid = Actual price + VAT
    <br>
    Amount paid = $1050 + $52.5
    <br>
    Amount paid = <strong>$1102.5</strong>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    <strong>Example 2</strong>
    <br>
    A firm paid $2835 per annum for water supply, the bill included VAT at 5% . 
    Find how much the actual bill is?
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    $2835 is 105% of the actual bill
    <br>
    1% of the actual bill = <sup>$2835</sup>&frasl;<sub>105</sub> = $27 
    <br>
    5% of the actual bill = $27 x 5 = $135
    <br>
    <strong>The actual bill</strong> = total bill – VAT
    <br>
    The actual bill = $2835 – $135
    <br>
    The actual bill = <strong>$2700</strong>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>
