<strong>Utility bills</strong> are based on the number of units consumed per period of time.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
An electricity meter reading changed from 6000 to 6235 over a period of one month. 
If the standing charge is $2 per month, the cost per unit is $0.8 and VAT is 5%. Calculate the total bill.
