<strong>Number of units consumed</strong> = Final reading - Initial reading
<br>
Number of units consumed = 6235 – 6000
<br>
Number of units consumed = <strong>235units</strong>
<br>
Cost of units consumed = $0.8 x 235
<br>
Cost of units consumed = <strong>$188</strong>
<br>
<strong>Total cost</strong> = Cost of units consumed + standing charges
<br>
= $188 + $2
<br>                 
 Total cost = $190
 <br>
Total bill including VAT = $190 x 105%
<br>
= $190 x <sup>105</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub>
<br>
= <sup>19950</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub>
<br>
Total bill = <strong>$199.5</strong>
</p>
