  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>How to Calculate Depreciation and Appreciation</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Depreciation</h3>
  </div>
  <p>
  <strong>Depreciation </strong> means loss in value. It could be as a result of wear and tear, damage etc. 
  </p>
  <p>
  <strong>Example 1</strong>
  <br>
  The cost of a machine is $520000; it depreciates by 10% in its first year and 15% in its second year. Find its value or worth after 2 years.
  <br>
  <strong>Solution</strong>
  <br>
  <strong>1<sup>st</sup> year; </strong>
  <br>
  Depreciation = 10% x 520000 = <sup>10</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x  <sup>520000</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> = <strong>$52000</strong>
  <br>
  Value at the end of 1<sup>st</sup> year = $520000 - $52000 = <strong>$468000</strong>
  <br>
  <strong>2<sup>nd</sup> year:</strong>
  <br>
  Depreciation = 15% of $468000
  <br>
  Depreciation = <sup>15</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x 468000 = 15 x 4680
  <br>
  Depreciation = <strong>$70200</strong>
  <br>
  Value at the end of 2<sup>nd</sup> year = $468000 - $70200
  <br>
  The value of the machine after 2 years = <strong>$397800</strong>	
  </p>
  <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> Appreciation </h3>
  </div>
  <p>
  <strong>Appreciation</strong> means increase in value. It could be as a result of civilization, development etc.
  </p>
<p>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
A man bought a piece of land at $2500. It appreciates at 15% in the first year and 25% in the second year due to rapid urban development. Calculate the value of the land after two years.
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
<strong>1<sup>st</sup> year;</strong>
<br>
Appreciation = 15% of $2500 = <sup>15</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x <sup>$2500</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> = 15 x 25 = <strong>$375</strong>
<br>
Value at the end of 1<sup>st</sup> year = $2500 + $375 = <strong>$2875</strong>
<br>
<strong>2<sup>nd</sup> year;</strong>
<br>
Appreciation = 25% of $2875 = <sup>25</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x <sup>$2875</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> = <sup>71875</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> = <strong>$718.75</strong>
<br>
Value of the land after two years = $2875 + $718.75 = <strong>$3593.75</strong>
</p>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>How to Calculate Inflation</h3>
</div>
<p>
<strong>Inflation</strong> is the loss in value of money due to rise in price.There are hyper-inflation, demand-pull inflation etc.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
A television set costs $1200. Find the cost of purchasing the same kind of TV set in 2 years’ time, if the inflation rate is 15% per annum.
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
1<sup>st</sup> year;
<br>
<strong>Inflation</strong> = 15% of $1200 = <sup>15</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x 1200 = 15 x 12 = <strong>$180</strong>
<br>
Cost at the end of the 1<sup>st</sup> year = $1200 + $180 = <strong>$1380</strong>
<br>
