<br>
Cost at the end of the 1<sup>st</sup> year = $1200 + $180 = <strong>$1380</strong>
<br>
2<sup>nd</sup> year;
<br>
<strong>Inflation</strong> = 15% of $1380 = <sup>15</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> x <sup>1380</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> = <sup>20700</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> = <strong>$207</strong>
<br>
<strong>The cost in 2 years’ time</strong> = $1380 + $207 = <strong>$1587</strong>
</p>
